t-weight:400;line-height:29px;text-align:left;\"><p style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"></p><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong>....none of which rise to the level of deserving a full newsletter but will nonetheless serve to start some compelling conversation.</strong> <a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/145028426?utm_id=d69348ad-561b-4671-bcd5-852a19a8915f&amp;utm_medium=email\" target=\"_blank\">I first did this back in December</a> and people seemed to really enjoy the format, so we'll try it again (also maybe, like me, you are also not quite ready to produce or consume fully formed thoughts).</p><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong>Discussed below: the runaway success of </strong><em><strong>Yesteryear</strong></em><strong>, the new tradwife-gets-her-comeuppance novel from Caro Claire Burke......why men aren't getting any of the few jobs that are being created in the US right now....the fantasy at the heart of </strong><em><strong>Shrinking</strong></em><strong>....and the imminent closure of Hampshire College.</strong></p><p style=\"margin:10px 0\">I hate paywalling stuff like this, but my strategy of \"people will pay for the stuff they read and like\" just doesn't work the way it used to. So if you've been meaning to subscribe and needed the nudge —&nbsp;just click on that prompt on the paywall below. If you're already a subscriber: I am so grateful for you. Thank you, as always, for making this community possible —&nbsp;and forward this email to your friends!</p><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong>👀 What You May Have Missed From The Extended Culture Study Universe 👀</strong></p><ul><li><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/hard-proof-that-156113766?utm_id=d69348ad-561b-4671-bcd5-852a19a8915f&amp;utm_medium=email\" target=\"_blank\">Hard Proof that Abortion Bans Are Bad For Business</a></strong></p></li><li><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/whats-with-all-156246037?utm_id=d69348ad-561b-4671-bcd5-852a19a8915f&amp;utm_medium=email\" target=\"_blank\">Unpacking All This Nostalgia for 2007-2008</a></strong></p></li><li><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/tuesday-thread-156110521?utm_id=d69348ad-561b-4671-bcd5-852a19a8915f&amp;utm_medium=email\" target=\"_blank\">Tuesday Thread: What Are You Reading?? (In April)</a></strong></p></li><li><p style=\"margin:10px 0\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/how-i-learned-to-155795977?utm_id=d69348ad-561b-4671-bcd5-852a19a8915f&amp;utm_medium=email\" target=\"_blank\">How I Learned to Stop Chasing Instant Hobby Mastery</a></strong><strong> (the comments are really lovely on this one)</strong></p></li></ul><div><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/posts/things-i-have-in-156553230?utm_campaign=free_member_locked_newsletter&amp;utm_source=post_link&amp;post_id=156553230&amp;media_id=652682781&amp;utm_id=d69348ad-561b-4671-bcd5-852a19a8915f&amp;utm_medium=email\">\r\n        <table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0px;\">\r\n        <tbody>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"width:592px;padding-top:8px;padding-bottom:8px;\">\r\n                <img style=\"border:none;display:block;font-size:13px;height:auto;outline:none;text-decoration:none;width:100%\" src=\"https://c10.patreonusercontent.com/4/patreon-media/p/post/156553230/fbbc1aeb03414ae489944732827f316d/eyJhIjoxLCJ3Ijo4MjB9/1.png?token-hash=EATyAzVKreeu-xKJVTcp1WPXipkZuZ-uqNRBnElFQYo%3D&amp;token-time=1778457600\" width=\"592\" height=\"auto\">\r\n            </td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n      </table>\r\n        </a></div><p style=\"margin:10px 0\">Last week, <em><a href=\"https://bookshop.org/a/56144/9780593804216\" target=\"_blank\">Yesteryear</a></em> debuted at #2 on the New York Times Bestseller list. This is a <em>wild</em> accomplishment for a debut novelist — even one with a popular podcast. It was <a href=\"https://deadline.com/2024/07/anne-hathaway-yesteryear-movie-amazon-mgm-caro-claire-burke-1236027903/\" target=\"_blank\">swiftly optioned</a> by Amazon MGM for a film adaptation with Anne Hathaway attached to star (and four studios bidding). I've never seen <em>so many</em> people comment that they're reading (or have already devoured) a recently released book in the \"What Are You Reading\" thread...</p><p></p></div></td></tr>\r\n </tbody></table></div><!--[if mso | IE]>\r\n</td></tr></table>\r\n<![endif]--></td></tr></tbody></table></div><!--[if mso | IE]>\r\n</td></tr></table>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n <!--[if mso | IE]>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"row-mb-pd-outlook\" style=\"width:600px;\" width=\"600\"><tr><td style=\"line-height:0px;font-size:0px;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;\">\r\n<![endif]--><div class=\"row-mb-pd\" style=\"margin:0px auto;max-width:600px;\"><table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"direction:ltr;font-size:0px;padding:16px 4px;text-align:center;vertical-align:top;\"><!--[if mso | IE]>\r\n<table role=\"presentation\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr><td style=\"line-height:0px;font-size:0px;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;\">\r\n<![endif]--><!--[if mso | IE]>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"mb-pd-cr-outlook card-pd-32-outlook mb-crd-pd-outlook\" style=\"width:592px;\" width=\"592\"><tr><td style=\"line-height:0px;font-size:0px;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;\">\r\n<![endif]--><div class=\"mb-pd-cr card-pd-32 mb-crd-pd\" style=\"background-color:#F5F5F5;border-radius:8px;margin:0px auto;max-width:592px;\"><table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background-color:#F5F5F5;border-collapse:separate;border-radius:8px;width:100%;\"><tbody>